President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Louisiana due to the conditions resulting from Tropical Storm Harvey. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security's Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, and emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. William J. Doran III has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.